{
  "stem": "11964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was part of a middle-class Jewish family consisting of my father, my mother, and my older sister, and later on my younger sister, who came along later on.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we live in a town of Radomsko, which counted probably about 30,000 to 33,000 inhabitants, 10% of whom were Jews.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jewish community was a very close community.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It seems to me that everybody knew everybody.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was also a community which suffered from some kind of class division.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Middle-class people were, of course, the better-to-do people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "These were the better-to-do merchants.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then there were the artisans, who did not fare as well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This really mostly manifested itself in the opportunities that we had, most especially in educational opportunities.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, as long back as I remember, I never went to public schools.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I went to private schools.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there were two reasons for it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "One, there were no schools of high school level which were public schools that were open to Jews, so the necessity of educating the children was to create a private school, private high school.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And because public schools were really not very keen on having Jewish students and Jewish pupils, that private school extended itself to the lowest grades as well.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I remember going straight from a kindergarten into this Jewish private school from which I matriculated with a degree, with a high school degree, which was called matura, M-A-T-U-R-A, which obviously connoted maturation.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The education that I received in this Jewish high school, which was called gymnasium-- and because it was a private school, it was under the direction of a lady whose name was Ludwiga Weintraub.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the actual name of the school was Jewish Gymnasium by Ludwiga Weintraub.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had very, very good professors, very good.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
